				 Lifer flees hospital

 A STAFF REPORTER
																								Calcutta, Dec. 29: Uttam Dulal Mondal, a murder convict serving a life sentence, escaped from Calcutta Medical College and Hospital this morning.
																								Sources said Mondal, 30, had been brought to the hospital from Alipore Central Jail 16 days ago for gall bladder surgery. 
																								Police officers said the two constables deployed outside Mondals ward had been suspended. 
																								Around 6.10 this morning, a ward boy discovered that Mondal was missing, a hospital official said, adding that the constables had probably dozed off. 

